The Yorkshire puddings come out best when the batter has been rested for at least one night, however they can be
cooked immediately after forming the batter if time requires it. Form the batter as directed in step 1 and
immediately proceed to step 2 without refrigerating it. The quantity of batter doesn't divide easily into standard 6-
well popover pans, but you can scale up the recipe by 50% in order to make a full 12 popovers instead of 8. If using
skim or low-fat milk, omit the water and increase amount of milk to 200g (7 ounces; 1 cup minus 2 tablespoons).
